				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Then it'd require a mapper that has both CHR-ROM and CHR-RAM, such as TQROM. And even then I'm not sure it'd be feasible, in the case of 5x10 tiles sized characters, we'd have to rewrite aprox. 3 columns and maybe 6 or 7 tiles height for both characters, so 48 tiles, definitely not doable at 60 FPS. Even if we limit to 2 colums (that would work, but not allow any other sprites, as each character would use 4 tiles) we'd have to rewrite at least 24 tiles, and that's still too much.<br /><br />I didn't even approach the huge problem it's going to be with palettes, but it seem like a poor idea overall. Either using only sprites or using one character sprite + one character BG are the most sensible solutions.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

